---
import PeriwinkleWebGPU from "../components/PeriwinkleWebGPU.astro";
---

<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
  <title>Periwinkle WebGPU Demo</title>
  <style>
    * {
      margin: 0;
      padding: 0;
      box-sizing: border-box;
    }

    body {
      font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, sans-serif;
      line-height: 1.6;
      overflow-x: hidden;
    }

    .demo-content {
      position: relative;
      z-index: 1;
      min-height: 300vh;
      color: white;
      text-shadow: 0 2px 16px rgba(150, 160, 255, 0.6);
      padding: 2rem;
    }

    .hero {
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      align-items: center;
      justify-content: center;
      min-height: 100vh;
      text-align: center;
      padding: 2rem;
    }

    .hero h1 {
      font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 8vw, 6rem);
      font-weight: 100;
      margin-bottom: 1rem;
      letter-spacing: -0.02em;
      background: linear-gradient(135deg, #fff 0%, #e6e9ff 100%);
      -webkit-background-clip: text;
      -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
      background-clip: text;
    }

    .hero p {
      font-size: clamp(1.2rem, 3vw, 1.8rem);
      font-weight: 300;
      opacity: 0.9;
      max-width: 600px;
      margin-bottom: 3rem;
    }

    .features {
      display: grid;
      gap: 3rem;
      max-width: 1200px;
      margin: 0 auto;
      padding: 4rem 2rem;
    }

    .feature {
      background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.08);
      backdrop-filter: blur(12px);
      border-radius: 16px;
      padding: 2.5rem;
      border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1);
      transition: transform 0.3s ease, background 0.3s ease;
    }

    .feature:hover {
      transform: translateY(-4px);
      background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.12);
    }

    .feature h3 {
      font-size: 1.5rem;
      margin-bottom: 1rem;
      color: #e6e9ff;
    }

    .feature p {
      opacity: 0.85;
      line-height: 1.7;
    }

    .tech-details {
      max-width: 800px;
      margin: 4rem auto;
      padding: 2rem;
      background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3);
      backdrop-filter: blur(16px);
      border-radius: 20px;
      border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.15);
    }

    .tech-details h2 {
      color: #e6e9ff;
      margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
      text-align: center;
    }

    .tech-list {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(250px, 1fr));
      gap: 1.5rem;
      list-style: none;
    }

    .tech-list li {
      padding: 1rem;
      background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.05);
      border-radius: 8px;
      border-left: 3px solid #aab2ff;
    }

    .interaction-guide {
      text-align: center;
      padding: 4rem 2rem;
      max-width: 600px;
      margin: 0 auto;
    }

    .interaction-guide h2 {
      color: #e6e9ff;
      margin-bottom: 2rem;
    }

    .guide-grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(200px, 1fr));
      gap: 1.5rem;
      margin-top: 2rem;
    }

    .guide-item {
      padding: 1.5rem;
      background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1);
      border-radius: 12px;
      border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.15);
    }

    .guide-item strong {
      color: #e6e9ff;
      display: block;
      margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    }

    @media (max-width: 768px) {
      .features {
        padding: 2rem 1rem;
      }

      .feature {
        padding: 1.5rem;
      }

      .tech-details {
        margin: 2rem 1rem;
        padding: 1.5rem;
      }
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <PeriwinkleWebGPU />

  <div class="demo-content">
    <section class="hero">
      <h1>Periwinkle Dreams</h1>
      <p>Experience the wonder of WebGPU rendering with procedural nebulas, sparkling stars, and interactive parallax effects</p>
    </section>

    <section class="features">
      <div class="feature">
        <h3>‚ú® WebGPU Powered</h3>
        <p>Utilizes cutting-edge WebGPU technology with WGSL shaders for maximum performance and stunning visual effects. Automatically falls back to WebGL when WebGPU isn't available.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="feature">
        <h3>üåå Procedural Nebula</h3>
        <p>Dynamic fractal brownian motion (FBM) generates ethereal nebula patterns that shift and flow in real-time, creating an ever-changing cosmic backdrop.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="feature">
        <h3>‚≠ê Multi-Scale Stars</h3>
        <p>Three layers of procedurally generated stars with different scales and twinkling frequencies create depth and richness in the stellar field.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="feature">
        <h3>üé≠ Interactive Parallax</h3>
        <p>Mouse movement and scroll position influence the parallax effect, making the cosmic environment respond to your exploration.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="interaction-guide">
      <h2>Interactive Features</h2>
      <p>The starfield responds to your interaction:</p>

      <div class="guide-grid">
        <div class="guide-item">
          <strong>Mouse Movement</strong>
          Move your cursor to create subtle parallax shifts in the nebula and stars
        </div>

        <div class="guide-item">
          <strong>Scroll Position</strong>
          Scroll up and down to see the cosmic backdrop shift with depth
        </div>

        <div class="guide-item">
          <strong>Reduced Motion</strong>
          Automatically respects your accessibility preferences for reduced motion
        </div>

        <div class="guide-item">
          <strong>Responsive Design</strong>
          Adapts to different screen sizes and pixel densities for optimal quality
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="tech-details">
      <h2>Technical Implementation</h2>
      <ul class="tech-list">
        <li><strong>WebGPU Compute:</strong> Hardware-accelerated rendering with modern GPU pipeline</li>
        <li><strong>WGSL Shaders:</strong> Custom vertex and fragment shaders written in WebGPU Shading Language</li>
        <li><strong>Procedural Generation:</strong> Real-time noise functions for nebula and star patterns</li>
        <li><strong>Fallback Support:</strong> Graceful degradation to Canvas 2D when WebGPU unavailable</li>
        <li><strong>Performance Optimized:</strong> 60fps rendering with minimal CPU overhead</li>
        <li><strong>Accessibility:</strong> Respects prefers-reduced-motion settings</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section style="padding: 4rem 2rem; text-align: center;">
      <h2 style="color: #e6e9ff; margin-bottom: 1rem;">Keep Scrolling</h2>
      <p style="opacity: 0.8;">Notice how the cosmic backdrop shifts as you explore...</p>
    </section>

    <section style="padding: 4rem 2rem; text-align: center;">
      <h2 style="color: #e6e9ff; margin-bottom: 1rem;">Endless Wonder</h2>
      <p style="opacity: 0.8; max-width: 600px; margin: 0 auto;">
        This WebGPU-powered starfield demonstrates the potential of modern web graphics.
        The combination of procedural generation, real-time rendering, and interactive
        effects creates an immersive experience that pushes the boundaries of what's
        possible in the browser.
      </p>
    </section>
  </div>
</body>
</html>